 years, was educated in Austria. His early career was in journalism. In 1931 he joined the Communist Party of Germany but, disillusioned, he resigned from it in 1938 and in 1940 published a devastating anti-Communist novel, \u003ci\u003eDarkness at Noon\u003c/i\u003e, which propelled him to instant international fame.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eOver the next forty-three years he espoused many causes, wrote novels and biographies, and numerous essays. In 1968 he was awarded the prestigious and valuable Sonning Prize \"For outstanding contribution to European culture\", and in 1972 he was made a \"Commander of the British Empire\" (CBE).\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eIn 1976 he was diagnosed with Parkinson's disease and three years later with leukaemia in its terminal stages. He committed suicide in 1983 in London.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e","isGrAuthor":false,"works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":94},"profileImageUrl":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/authors/1256757331i/17219._UX200_CR0,49,200,200_.jpg","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/17219.Arthur_Koestler","user":null,"viewerIsFollowing":null,"followers":{"__typename":"ContributorFollowersConnection","totalCount":1130}},"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.Xix4q4hFCjFyst3vlRShSQ":{"id":"kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.Xix4q4hFCjFyst3vlRShSQ","__typename":"Contributor","name":"Daphne Hardy","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/460050.Daphne_Hardy","isGrAuthor":false},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.iaGnl6q3uoMwdNp55YSWfA":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.iaGnl6q3uoMwdNp55YSWfA","__typename":"Book"},"User:3427339":{"id":3427339,"__typename":"User","legacyId":3427339,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1301087352i/3427339._UX200_CR0,45,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":1237,"viewableName":"Jeffrey Keeten","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https